Boryspil International Airport, KievThe Global Times on Saturday obtained satellite images from spacety, a satellite data service provider, on some hot spots of the ongoing military conflict in Ukraine, including the two major airports in Kiev and Kharkiv, Ukraine air force base in Melitopol, and Odessa port. Comparison of images taken before and after the crossfire between Russia and Ukraine which broke out on Thursday showed more than 10 armored vehicles on the runways of Kiev international airport as well as a large aircraft. The airport cannot provide take-off and landing services, as the runways and taxiways were occupied by the military vehicles. 

Kharkiv International AirportThe situation looks similar at the airport in Kharkiv, the second largest city of Ukraine. 

Port of OdessaFacilities at the Black Sea port of Odessa appeared intact as of the time the image was taken. 

Melitopol air base The number of transport aircraft at the air strip in Melitopol has been reduced significantly, but some aircraft are still there. Russian Defense Ministry claimed on Saturday that its troops have taken control of  the city in southeastern Ukraine.